KATERINI vied between rivals into the first turn, cleared and crossed over to the rail around that bend, set all the pace to the top of the lane, remained clear into the furlong grounds, challenged with a sixteenth remaining and yielded to the winner. SHEZMISBEHAVING traveled in the two path towards the rear, had to steady midway up the backstretch, eased out to the four path on the far turn and lacked further response. CORPORAL VIOLETTE (IRE) pulled along the inside and had to steady off heels early, continued to tug the rider along, steadied into the far turn, tipped out to the two path and weakened. DOWNBURST settled off the pace three then two wide, went three deep into the second turn, came four wide into the lane and weakened. MODERA brushed with outer rival at the start, vied for the lead from inside while pulling into the first turn, steadied around the bend and dropped back to stalk, tracked along the inside into the far turn, cut the corner into the lane and faded.

JACKS OUTLAW stalked along the inside, tugged the rider along early on the backstretch, raced in mid-pack two wide into the second bend, came out in the lane and lacked a bid. MAJESTIC EAGLE settled next to the rail, moved out in the middle stages and exited the backstretch three deep, angled back to the inside around the far turn and could not rally. GRAPE NUTS WARRIOR steadied briefly between rivals, moved into the two path to stalk the pacesetter, roused three then four wide on the second bend and weakened. BIRTH OF COOL raced up close from outside into the first turn, applied pressure at the nine-sixteenths pole but could not go on with the leader past the half-mile pole, chased two then three wide around the second bend, bothered a bit past the eighth pole but had already started to weaken. BOASTER may have broke a step slow but was content to trail early and steered to the inside, saved ground to the far turn and was never a factor.
